The Semaphore is the integer value which is used to achieve process synchronization.
Semaphore is used to work in a condition where a process can work concurrently.

Semaphore S can have 2 variables
    wait()
    Signal()

The types of semaphore
    Binary Semaphore
    Counter Semaphore
Binary Semaphore-Range Between 0 and 1
    Known as Mutex locks as the locks provide mutual exclusion
Counter Semaphore-Range That is specified
    Used to control access to a resource to a multiple instances.
